        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1745260949" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15004460046671843966"><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>&quot;Ever had that happen? Once you can’t have something, you want it that much more.” <br/>“Yes,” he said bitterly. “It happens all the time.”</b>
  </i>
</blockquote><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1454802725ra/18016214.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>&quot;I don&apos;t care if he&apos;s not the emotional type or the complimentary type or what. No one can look at you in this dress, in all that fire and gold, and start talking about anachronisms. If I were him, I would have said, &apos;You are the most beautiful creature I have ever seen walking this earth.” </b>
  </i>
</blockquote><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1460194272ra/18710518.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>“Sage?&quot; Adrian lightly touched my arm, and</b></i></blockquote></span>
  <span id="freeText15004460046671843966" style="display:none"><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>"Ever had that happen? Once you can’t have something, you want it that much more.” <br>“Yes,” he said bitterly. “It happens all the time.”</b>
  </i>
</blockquote><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1454802725ra/18016214.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>"I don't care if he's not the emotional type or the complimentary type or what. No one can look at you in this dress, in all that fire and gold, and start talking about anachronisms. If I were him, I would have said, 'You are the most beautiful creature I have ever seen walking this earth.” </b>
  </i>
</blockquote><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1460194272ra/18710518.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>“Sage?" Adrian lightly touched my arm, and I jumped at the feel of his fingertips against my skin. "You okay?"<br>"I don't know," I said softly. "I just thought of something crazy."<br>"Welcome to my world.”</b>
  </i>
</blockquote><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1504005914ra/23715121.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>Ohhhh my god!!!! I love it!!! I love Adrian so much &lt;3 &lt;3 And right now I hate Sydney! First Rose and now Sydney! Why they keep hurting Adrian? Just give him to me :P<br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1496729406ra/22946178.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>------------------------------------------------<br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1501927455i/23511022._SY540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>------------------------------------------------<br><br>1)A lot of things happen in this book but all I can think about is that kiss! Oh my god! It rocked my world and Sydney's even though she doesn't want to admit! And then he admits his feelings about Sydney(shock) but she was like "ohh I am human ..you are vampire... we can not be together...BULLSHIT"<br>My poor Adrian. Once again he is hurting.<br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1452968120ra/17767568.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>“And I don’t choose you. That’s what you’re missing in all of this.” <br>Adrian stilled. His smile dropped. “I don’t believe you.” <br>I scoffed. “Let me guess. Because I kissed you back?” That kiss had made me feel more alive than I had in weeks, and I had a feeling he knew that. <br>He shook his head. “No. Because there’s no one else out there who understands you like I do.”</b>
  </i>
</blockquote><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1503577153ra/23676765.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>2)In the entire book Adrian found excuses to be around Sydney(He acted like he didn't know how to drive) and she didn't get it until the end of the book. It was so obvious.<br><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>“Sage," he said. "What are you wearing?"<br>I sighed and stared down at the dress. "I know. It's red. Don't start. I'm tired of hearing about it."<br>"Funny," he said. "I don't think I could ever get tired of looking at it.” </b>
  </i>
</blockquote><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1456064833ra/18185961.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>“You need me? You yell. You want to leave? We go. I'll get you out of here, no matter what.”</b>
  </i>
</blockquote><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1504005914ra/23715122.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>See? He says all those things and she is completely oblivious.<br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1455905624ra/18167449.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>3)Hayden?No! Brandon? No... Brayden! That's right. Almost everyone forgets his name except for Sydney and Trey. So, that guy is Sydney's love interest!<br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1462420217ra/18994858.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>The only thing Sydney and Brayden have in common is that they are both smart! Their dates were boring and a little bit funny(shake hands). Their kisses was not memorable. She didn't feel anything when they were kissing. In the end, Brayden broke up with Sydney. We were all glad about it.<br><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>“You're in an awfully good mood," he observed. "Was there a sale at Khakis-R-Us?” <br>"Nope. Brayden broke up with me."</b>
  </i>
</blockquote><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1504005914ra/23715123.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>I also liked Adrian's jealousy. Of course!<br><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>“Really, Sage? A date?”<br>I sighed. “Yes, Adrian. A date.”<br>“A real date. Not, like, doing homework together,” he added.<br>“I mean like where you go out to a movie or something. And a movie that’s not part of a school assignment. Or about something boring.”<br>“A real date.”</b>
  </i>
</blockquote><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1493713713ra/22644116.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br> <br>4)Vampire hunters exists after all. And guess what? Trey is one of them. I did not see that coming. Although I still like Trey. He is so funny and cute. He is not the bad guy here. He is a lot like Sydney. He grow up believing what they told him.<br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1504005914ra/23715124.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>5)Sonya, Adrian and Dimitri are doing some experiments to determine the changes a person who has been restored to Strigoi. Especially, Adrian is very "happy" about it.<br><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>“Day 24. Situation is growing worse. My captors continue to find new and horrific ways to torture me. When not working, Agent Scarlet spends her days examining fabric swatches for bridesmaid dresses and going on about how in love she is. This usually causes Agent Boring Borscht to regale us with stories of Russian weddings that are even more boring than his usual ones. My attempts at escape have been thwarted thus far. Also, I am out of cigarettes. Any assistance or tobacco products you can send will be greatly appreciated.<br>-Prisoner 24601” </b>
  </i>
</blockquote><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1504005914ra/23715125.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br> <br>Adrian is also really really happy about the fact that he spends a lot of time with Dimitri!<br><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>“What do you think Dimitri? Is this a good idea, Dimitri? Please give us your blessing so that we can fall down and worship you, Dimitri.” </b>
  </i>
</blockquote><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1494257538ra/22698385.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>Anyway, once again Sonya is in trouble. Vampire hunter or the "Warriors" believe that Sonya is still Strigoi and they wanted to kill her. They kidnapped her but Sydney, Eddie, Dimitri and Adrian rescued her.<br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1504005914ra/23715126.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>6)Adrian's father. What an asshole! He wanted to know how his mother was and he treat Adrian like shit. He also blamed him that it was his fault that his mother was in prison!Asshole!<br>I will admit though that Adrian did some things on purpose.<br><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>“Adrian ordered a martini, earning disapproving looks from his father and me.<br>'It's barely noon,' said Nathan.<br>'I know,' said Adrian. 'I'm surprised I held out that long too.”</b>
  </i>
</blockquote><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1496443922ra/22913626.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>But something good came up out of that disastrous meeting!<br><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>“The other thing that bothered me… well, he said all that in front of you.”<br>“Don’t worry about me. I’ve been with much more abrasive people than him.”<br>“No, no… I mean…” Adrian looked at me and then quickly averted his eyes. “After what he said about me, I can’t stand the thought that you might think less of me.”<br>"Adrian.” I laid my hand over his and felt a warm spark of connection. He jerked his head toward me in astonishment. “Nothing he said could change what I think of you. I’ve had my mind made up about you for a long time… and it’s all good.”</b>
  </i>
</blockquote><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1461408886ra/18863215.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>7)Even though Jill and Micah were cute together, I am glad that they break up! They are better as friends.<br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1455409508ra/18099005.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>8) I loved Angeline! At first she had some adjusting problems. In other words, she was always in trouble. I loved it! But in the end she became more responsible and Eddie saw that change and she ask her out. I love Angeline but I want Eddie with Jill. Eddie is in love with Jill and Jill likes him. What a mess.<br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1456262426ra/18212004.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>9)I also loved the self-defense classes Sydney and Adrian were taking. Wolf was awesome.<br><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>“You were totally unprepared for her.”<br>“That's for damned sure.” </b>
  </i>
</blockquote><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1489690814ra/22240559.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"></span>
