<span id="freeTextContainer10849604805585125219"><b>2019</b><br/><br/>Just as amazing 2nd time around!!!!<br/><br/><b>2012</b><br/><br/>OH.MY.GOD!!!<br/><br/>I have to say that I loved book 1, it unexpectedly took me to knew heights and a totally different route to Dimitri&apos;s and Rose&apos;s. I had no idea that this new path would just over-take one of my all-time favourite series Vampire Academy...<br/><br/>Let me just tell you, Adrian was a likeable character, a character I could think of a mediocre or average but likeable just the same... somewhere along the line, mostly this book, Adrian began to tug at me, </span>
  <span id="freeText10849604805585125219" style="display:none"><b>2019</b><br /><br />Just as amazing 2nd time around!!!!<br /><br /><b>2012</b><br /><br />OH.MY.GOD!!!<br /><br />I have to say that I loved book 1, it unexpectedly took me to knew heights and a totally different route to Dimitri's and Rose's. I had no idea that this new path would just over-take one of my all-time favourite series Vampire Academy...<br /><br />Let me just tell you, Adrian was a likeable character, a character I could think of a mediocre or average but likeable just the same... somewhere along the line, mostly this book, Adrian began to tug at me, whether this was through the times I simply creased up at his sense of humour, or maybe the times I beveled at his pain... somewhere along the line I simply fell in love with him, move over Dimitri, Adrian step inside!!!<br /><br />This book had me from the beginning, my adorable Sydney is growing up fast and she grabs me everytime! Jill is taking on much more of a staring role now and even Eddie and the new Angeline are main characters in their own right...<br /><br />I wasn't ever sure that Richelle Mead could compare her new series to Vampire Academy and truthfully, she doesn't have to, this series is FREAKIN FABULOUS in its own right and I can't wait for book 3....<br /><br />I simply can't put into words how fantastic this series really is - I LOVE IT!!!!</span>
  <a data-text-id="10849604805585125219" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
