    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_202775922" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/202775922" />
    <a title="Darlene" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5835643-darlene"><img alt="Darlene" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1427085895p2/5835643.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/202775922?book_show_action=true">Aug 27, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Darlene" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Darlene" href="/user/show/5835643-darlene">Darlene</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer202775922" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4324712519062979443">What to say, what to say…<br/><br/>Well, I love <i>The Golden Lily</i>. Love it, love it, love it. I had been waiting anxiously for this book for a while, and it did not disappoint me. I won’t lie, these first two <i>Bloodlines</i> books are very predictable, but there’s so much charm and quality that you don’t even care.<br/><br/>First, this is cast of very likeable characters. There’s our protagonist, Sydney, whom I love. Sydney is smart, but naïve, and very much awkward. It’s kind of unexpected, considering how cool and compo</span>
  <span id="freeText4324712519062979443" style="display:none">What to say, what to say…<br><br>Well, I love <i>The Golden Lily</i>. Love it, love it, love it. I had been waiting anxiously for this book for a while, and it did not disappoint me. I won’t lie, these first two <i>Bloodlines</i> books are very predictable, but there’s so much charm and quality that you don’t even care.<br><br>First, this is cast of very likeable characters. There’s our protagonist, Sydney, whom I love. Sydney is smart, but naïve, and very much awkward. It’s kind of unexpected, considering how cool and composed she seems, but under all that is a teenage girl with insecurities like any other. She’s cute and very relatable with her own strengths and weaknesses to go around. You get to see her grow more throughout this book.<br>Adrian… *sighs dreamily and stares into space*. Adrian has always been my favorite character of the VA series, and all you Dimitri fangirls are going to realize just how awesome he is sooner or later, maybe during this book, maybe later. He is just this sexy piece of complex art. There are so many emotions behind that wit. Love him &lt;3<br>Jill didn’t annoy me as much as in <i>Bloodlines</i>. She’s maturing. And I’m not even sure if it was really Jill that annoyed me or her love life. Eddie’s awesome as ever. Angeline made a great, fun addition to the group. She is hilarious!<br>Individually, they might not be super interesting, but together this group is totally adorable. What’s awesome is that they really are like a family, even with all those romantic entanglements xD<br><br>Yeah, this book has its fair share of romance. SYDRIAN fans won’t be disappointed, just hungry for more. This is definitely one of my favorite couples. Richelle Mead, you are genius for putting them together. Opposites in every way possible, they complement each other <i>perfectly</i>. They make each other better people and know the little things about each other. <br><br><i>"But when I’m around you, I want to be better because… well, because it feels right. Because I want to. You make me want to become something greater than myself. I want to excel. You inspire me in every act, every word, every glance. I look at you, and you’re like… like light made into flesh."<br><br>"You are the most beautiful creature I have ever seen walking this earth."<br><br>"'The slush. That thing's like 99 percent sugar. You just drank one, Sage.'<br>'Maybe you drank liquid sugar. Mine was sugar free.' I hoped I sounded convincing."<br><br>“You're in an awfully good mood," he observed. "Was there a sale at Khakis-R-Us?”</i><br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380308444ra/688162.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>Aiden-Brady-Hayden-Brandon was okay, though not all that memorable. Now that he’s out of the way I wonder who will fill his space in the other end of the love triangle. Trey (who I actually really like) has a lot in common with Sydney, and there’s always that Ian guy from <i>The Last Sacrifice</i>. This is assuming there will be a love triangle of course. But this is Richelle Mead, guys. And a Richelle Mead book without a crazy love triangle? I doubts it. <br>Jill’s love life is… frustrating. After the whole Lee disaster, she found solace in Micah, and Eddie longingly watches all of this. Like I’ve said before, Eddie is the most deserving character in the entire VA /<i>Bloodlines</i> series. In all the seven books he has been in, he has done nothing but help everyone else. I don’t like the idea of him and Jill, but if she makes him happy, whatever. <br>Jill does the mature thing in breaking up with Micah, but right after she’s like “oh now that I’ve broken up with him, maybe I can go out with him!” and I’m just yanking my hair out. I love the idea of Eddie and Angeline! I had always seen Mia as a perfect match for him, seeing how they went through the same thing, but Angeline is great too. Their relationship is great. I’d like to see a strong, independent, single Jill anyways.<br><br>There isn’t much that much action in this book, but that’s only to be expected. We’re with an Alchemist and an Ivashkov. But they’re learning, there are four more books to go, and Sydney will learn to use a gun! This book leaned mostly on romance and character development. And that vampire hunter thing. I loved it all, except for the magic thing. Witches are the last thing I expected in this series, and I can’t say I want to see more of that.<br><br>Nevertheless, I can’t wait for the next book.<i>The Indigo Spell</i> is what it's called. What the crap is that supposed to mean? Sounds witchy :/<br><br><s>One thing concerning Angeline bothered me, though. The book mentioned her having a ‘southern drawl’ and the Keepers being from the Appalachians, but wasn’t Angeline from Russia??? Confusion o_O</s><br>Just kidding. I was wrong :3 Thanks to all the people who corrected me<br><br><br>UPDATE 6/11/12<br>I read the first two chapters last night. Tomorrow's the day :D<br><br>UPDATE 2/14/12<br>Whoa, whoa, whoa who's this Brayden dude? What the heck happened to Trey &lt;&gt;_&lt;&gt;<br><br>8/27/11<br><br>Insanely excited for this book!!!!! The cover isn't very pretty though... except for Jill. The model looks like Dakota Blue Richards, whom I imagined for Jill. <br>Predictions~<br>•love triangle between Sydney, Adrian and Trey (wouldn't it be awesome if it was Ian?) and possibly Angeline. Oh wait, that'd be a love square.<br>•Jill ends up with Eddie or realizes she has feelings for him after she sees him with Angeline. I like EddiexAngeline much better.<br>•Dimitri will mess all this stuff up, but in the end bring Adrian and Sydney closer than ever before<br>•one of Sydney's sorority girl friends (Kristen and Julia) gets killed<br>•Laurel becomes more important<br>•Tasha kidnaps Jill<br><br>Things I think would be cool if they happened~<br>•Tasha coming back at all. Miss that evil lady.<br>•EddiexAngeline. Yeah...<br>•Jill, having mixed feelings for Micah and Eddie, unintentionally hurts both of them and ends up with neither boy. Call me a sadist, but it would be boring if everyone got together with everyone and they all carried each other off into the sunset.<br>•Ian instead of Trey :)<br>•Avery Lazar breaks out of that mental institution place and does all this crazy stuff!</span>
  <a data-text-id="4324712519062979443" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


